This product bundles no third-party source. Its sole runtime dependency,
`cryptography` (Apache-2.0 / BSD), is installed separately via pip and is not
redistributed here.

IMPORTANT — what this software is NOT:
This is a vertical slice that proves an architecture, not a hardened product.
The chef sandbox and the console identity are REAL and CI-proven (OS-enforced
sandboxes on Windows/Linux/macOS plus a real KVM virtual machine; Ed25519
signed-request auth verified against admin public keys). What is still MOCKED or
unbuilt: attestation (MockAttestor signs a code hash, not a TEE quote — a real
TEE giving hide-from-host + hardware attestation is the remaining frontier), the
kitchen (cooperative fixtures, not a provenance-signed store), SSO/OIDC
federation of the console keys, and a network (FastAPI) surface. See PROGRESS.md
for the full, unsoftened list. Do not deploy it as a security control without
replacing those remaining layers.
